konthai's decode logic and confidence/abstain discipline were calibrated against a
small, native-speaker-labelled eval set drawn from real obfuscated-Thai social text.
The ground-truth labels are the work of the repo owner (a native Thai speaker); they
are authoritative and should not be "corrected" against model intuition.

The repository packaging pattern (single-skill plugin layout, the cross-platform
SKILL.md compatibility checker, version-parity gate, and the product-voice spec
convention) is adapted from `sorawit-w/cerby` (MIT) — ideas and structure, not
verbatim prose. `scripts/check-skill-compat.py` is adapted from that project.
